Peel, core, and roughly chop the apples. Combine the apples, Â½ cup water, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon, and salt to a simmer in a heavy-bottomed, medium saucepan. Cover and cook over medium heat for 12-15 minutes, shaking the pan occasionally, until the apples are tender but juicy. Remove the cinnamon stick. Remove from the heat, Using a fork, beat in the butter. Serve hot or at room temperature.